con:testCase.con:description:
As a system requirement, transactions are unable to be deleted systematically (via request).   As a result, there 
are no requests or procedures availble to the general user to remove this test data from the database via some cleanup test case..   
As an alternative, the following DB script can be executed from within SQL Anywhere Interactive SQL Console to remove all transactions:

delete  SALES_ORDER_STATUS_HIST where so_id > 3000;
delete  CUSTOMER_ACTIVITY where xact_id > 30000;
delete  SALES_INVOICE where xact_id > 30000;
delete  xact where xact_id > 30000;
delete  ITEM_MASTER_STATUS_HIST where item_id > 200;
delete  SALES_ORDER_ITEMS where item_id > 200;
delete  SALES_ORDER where so_id > 3000;
delete  VENDOR_ITEMS;
delete  ITEM_MASTER where item_id > 200;
delete  customer where customer_id > 47;
commit;

Depending on the database instance these test cases are targeting, you may have to change the 
values of the SQL predicates match up with the target record ID's in order to bulk delete accurately.
